1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 Meaning of Urban Local Government

Urban Local Government refers to:

👉 Administration of towns and cities by local elected bodies.

📌 Constitutional status provided by:

74th Constitutional Amendment Act, 1992
🔵 Important Features of 74th Amendment

Added:

Part IX-A
12th Schedule

📌 Came into force in:

1993
🔹 Types of Urban Local Bodies
1️⃣ Municipal Corporation
Large cities
Example: Bengaluru, Mumbai
2️⃣ Municipality / Municipal Council
Smaller urban areas
3️⃣ Nagar Panchayat
Transitional area (rural → urban)
🔴 Composition

Members are:
👉 Directly elected by people.

Chairperson:

Mayor / President depending on body.
🔹 Ward Committees

Created in larger municipalities for:

Local participation
Better administration
🔹 Reservation

Reservation for:

SCs
STs
Women

📌 Minimum one-third seats reserved for women.

🔹 State Election Commission

Conducts elections to:

Municipalities
Panchayats

Every:
👉 5 years

🔹 State Finance Commission

Reviews financial condition of:

Urban local bodies
Panchayats
🔹 12th Schedule

Contains:
👉 18 subjects

Examples:

Urban planning
Water supply
Public health
Fire services
Urban forestry
🔹 Importance of Urban Local Bodies
Urban governance
Public services
Decentralization
Citizen participation
🔹 Difference Between Panchayats & Municipalities
Feature	Panchayats	Municipalities
Area	Rural	Urban
Amendment	73rd	74th
Schedule	11th	12th
